Antonius Musa's story is so inspiring to any medic, Augustus on his deathbed in agony, making preparations to pass his dealings on, having given his ring already, just a dead man passing away, then a maniac doctor comes and forces him into a cold bath to torture him back alive.

I really like stories of barbaric medics who just refuse to give up and brutalize their patients with wild and dangerous methods until somehow it actually works out and they get the cure, just going hardcore all in with zero regards for civility, respect for the dying, maniacs

There was 100% someone next to Augustus' pseudo-deathbed that tried to say like "let him die in peace, don't ruin his last moments with idiotic ice baths, just let nature take its course, it was his fate, etc." but it didn't matter. Go into the cold bath now. Kapitulieren? Nein.
